itemListElement.name: Seattle Pike Place Market Food Tour(Private)

name: Seattle Pike Place Market Food Tour(Private)
description:
Experience Seattles iconic Pike Place Market in the most unique way possible, by letting our local guides delight you with a fusion of Pacific Northwest staples and immigrant-inspired cuisine.

On this tour, youll get to know the history behind the market and the citizens who have helped preserve its character to this day. Youll get to meet the locals, perhaps spot some flying fish, and pass by two renown attractions: the notorious Gum Wall and the original Starbucks!

Youll also get to enjoy local eats from hearty seafood to fresh local cheeses and fruits. Well combine these local foods with cuisine inspired by immigrants who have brought their own style, ingredients, and stories to Seattle over the past century and a half.

You'll try a taste from one of the market's renowned bakeries followed up by something sweet to cap off your tour. While you eat, youll be even happier knowing youre supporting the market with your ticket price!

review.name: Private Tour of Pike Place Market
review.reviewBody: We got to see a lot of the market and enjoy many tastings, accommodating dietary restrictions and preferences. I definitely recommend leaving time to explore the market and do some shopping after your tour, but at least we had a better sense of WHERE we wanted to explore.

itemListElement.name: Private Seattle Coffee Culture Guided Tour

name: Private Seattle Coffee Culture Guided Tour
description:
Explore the evolution of coffee culture in the Pacific Northwest on this walking and tasting tour of Seattles Capitol Hill neighborhood!

Your local guide will keep you caffeinated as you delve into the history and roasting and creation processes behind the usual coffee shop orders as well as the citys more unique and specialty offerings. You may get to try anything from infused coffee to a decadent espresso invented right here in Seattle!

In addition to getting a crash course in everything from single-origin to sustainable coffees, youll really come to appreciate the closely associated counter culture that has historically been  and still is  prevalent in the Capitol Hill neighborhood.

Youll pass by music venues with historic ties to Seattles grunge and current EDM scene as well as plenty of places your guide can recommend for cocktails, live music, or even more coffee following your tour!

review.name: Great coffee tour with history
review.reviewBody: William was awesome, he waited for us since we had trouble finding the starting point. He was very informative and welcoming to all questions, coffee related or not. I will definitely be recommending him and this tour to my friends.

review.name: Short and sweet. We loved it.
review.reviewBody:
We walked a lot, drank some delicious coffee, very informative and nice to know the history of the original seattle.
We will definitely recommend this tour.

itemListElement.name: Preserving Pike Place: Market Community Tour

name: Preserving Pike Place: Market Community Tour
description:
Get a truly unique perspective of Seattles iconic Pike Place Market on this walking tour that gives back to the marketplace community! Your local guide will lead you through the maze of the market, exploring its evolution through the historic buildings and stories of vendors past and present.

Along the way, we may catch a show of the famous flying fish, pass by the oldest existing Starbucks, and make our way to one of the citys most unusual attractions, the Gum Wall.

While youll get to experience the most visited sites of the market, youll also receive a deep appreciation of the Pike Place Market Foundation and the array of services they provide to create a strong community that keeps the market going and benefits those in need.

Best yet, your ticket price already includes a donation to the Foundation, so youll be giving back to the community yourself!

itemListElement.name: Uncovering Seattle's Hidden Gems-Private Walking Tour

name: Uncovering Seattle's Hidden Gems-Private Walking Tour
description:
Seattles architecture and art scene is second to none. On this walking tour, youll get to see incredible works and get to know beautiful Uptown Seattle.

Well board the monorail for a quick ride to Seattle Center, home of the towering Space Needle, the mind-bending Museum of Pop Culture, and creative works meant to inspire, invite, and invoke the nature of the Pacific Northwest. Your guide will let you know how to arrange admission to any of the areas venues for after your tour.

Throughout the Center, well explore a nearby local radio studio, pass by a sustainable sports arena, and get a chance to stop in at some of the neighborhoods best coffee shops and bakeries.

With your pastry and beverage in hand, youll be ready to trek your way uphill to enjoy fabulous city skyline views or head out of the neighborhood to relax along the beautiful Puget Sound waterfront. Your guide will have plenty of recommendations for where to eat, drink, and sightsee in Seattle!

name: Seattle Cocktail Private Tour
description:
Your drinks are on us: On this tasting tour, youll enjoy three cocktails carefully selected by a local guide. Well start near Pioneer Square, where youll hear about the citys founding and historic preservation, its indigenous past, and the once-flourishing grunge scene that started right here in downtown Seattle.

We may get to visit one of the oldest restaurants in Seattle, a modern-day speakeasy, or just venues with great cocktails with fascinating backgrounds. Well enjoy time-honored libations, Prohibition-inspired creations, and tipples with a twist on the classics.

While youre sipping on excellently crafted cocktails, your guide will entertain with stories of Seattles gritty past, from unlikely beloved city criminals to the resurgence of cocktail culture in the 90s. And whether youre new to the cocktail scene or an aficionado, youll impress at your next party or outing thanks to your guides knowledge of the ingredients that go into making your mixed drink so delectable.

name: Seattle Art Museum Admission Ticket
description:
Marvel at diverse global collections of artworks at the Seattle Art Museum.

Immerse youself in one of a kind exhibitions, from ancient to modern art.

Explore remarkable Native American galleries with meaningful Northwest pieces.

Discover the incredible world of African, Asian, and Australian Aboriginal art.

Make the most of your experience by visiting Market Seattle and the gift shop.

name: MOPOP Museum Admission Ticket
description:
Watch music performances and light shows on a mammoth 60-foot HD LED screen in Sky Church.

Plug into a pixelated world of wonder in Indie Game Revolution, featuring 20 single and multiplayer games for the whole family to try.

Get lost in exhibits like Fantasy: Worlds of Myth and Magic, or face your fears in Scared to Death: The Thrill of Horror Films. For the full spaceship experience, head over to Infinite Worlds of Science Fiction.

Travel alongside the legendary Jimi Hendrix at the height of his fame in Wild Blue Angel: Hendrix Abroad, 1966-1970.

Journey through the early 90's Seattle punk scene with Nirvana: Taking Punk to the Masses.
